# Catalyst One — Layout Integrity & Content Safety Standard

**Status:** PERMANENT DESIGN RULE  
**This is not a feature.** It applies to every screen, widget, chart, tooltip, and future layout work.

---

## Primary Principle

**Business information is sacred.**

Under no circumstance should any text, card, chart, tooltip, button, or widget overlap another element.

If additional space is required, the **layout must adapt**.

Never force content into insufficient space.

---

## No Overlapping Rule

The application must never allow:

- Text over text
- Cards over charts
- Tooltips covering fixed / persistent information
- Buttons covering data
- Labels touching charts
- Tables clipping into widgets
- Components extending beyond their containers

These are **layout defects**.

---

## Adaptive Layout

When content grows, the layout must automatically:

- Increase container height
- Push subsequent sections downward
- Maintain spacing
- Preserve readability

The page should expand naturally. Prefer fluid growth over absolute stacking that causes collisions.

---

## Scrolling

If the page becomes taller, the page must remain **fully scrollable**.

Never compress content simply to fit within the viewport.

**Readability is always more important than reducing page height.**

Avoid nested scroll traps that hide overflow without a clear scroll affordance.

---

## Tooltips

Hover cards must never obscure persistent information.

Tooltips should intelligently reposition when insufficient space exists (flip / shift / collision avoidance). Prefer portals with collision detection over fixed absolute offsets that can land on KPIs, scores, or labels.

---

## Charts

- Charts should dynamically resize whenever necessary
- Labels should always remain **outside** the chart boundary
- Maintain comfortable spacing around every chart
- Never place HTML/SVG labels on top of the plot area when they can sit in a reserved margin or outer frame

---

## Validation (blocking)

A screen is **NOT production-ready** if:

- Any content overlaps
- Any information is clipped
- Any text becomes unreadable
- Any widget obscures another widget

These are **blocking issues** and must be resolved before the screen is considered complete.

---

## Relationship to other rules

- Complements `enterprise-screen-ux-standard.mdc` (hierarchy, above-the-fold, usability)
- Complements `data-integrity-analytics-standard.mdc` (accuracy of numbers)
- Complements `enterprise-accessibility-contrast.mdc` (contrast / readability)
- Complements `chanakya-radar.mdc` (Radar labels outside dial)

When space is tight: **adapt and scroll** — never overlap or clip sacred business information.
